	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001104_0001"/><!--pb/@n='80r'-->
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName><reg>,</reg> I shall feel obliged 
<lb/>if you add the titles of <persName>Sir Roderick</persName> as they appear in 
<lb/>his last Presidential address before the R.G.S. &amp; 
<lb/>send this dedication to the printer. As he is to be home 
<lb/>on <choice><reg>M</reg><orig>m</orig></choice>onday I would like him to see the proof &amp; he 
<lb/>might suggest some alteration. I have not been 
<lb/>able to get the preface finished though half done<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>This "lionizing" is very hard work but I am on my 
<lb/>way South &amp; will soon be done with it. I am quite 
<lb/>tired out. I am now with your namesake <persName>Murray</persName> of 
<lb/><placeName>Lintrose</placeName>, Cupar Angus but leave today &amp; if my mother 
<lb/>is better will go to <placeName>Kendal</placeName>, Westmoreland on <choice><reg>M</reg><orig>m</orig></choice>onday<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p>near <placeName>Dundee</placeName> 27<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Sept<hi rend="sup">r</hi> 1857 </p>
			
